STATIONARY SOURCE AND REGULATED SUBSTANCES

The Midmar West Plant stores and processes the following RMP-regulated substances: natural gasoline, natural gas liquids (NGL) and propane. NGL is a flammable mixture that contains propane, ethane, N-butane, isobutane, isopentane, N-pentane, and methane.  The stationary source determined to provide the worst case scenario is the Product Surge Tank. The Product Surge Tank contains NGLs. Ethane was used as the flammable in this scenario due to it being the only regulated flammable that exists in the mixture above the threshold quantity.

GENERAL ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION PROGRAM AND CHEMICAL-SPECIFIC PREVENTION STEPS

The Midmar West Plant maintains a consistent accidental release prevention program to eliminate or minimize releases of ethane. The Prevention Program required under 40 CFR 68 is identical to the prevention program required under OSHA's PSM. The Midmar West Plant's general accidental release prevention program  and chemical specific prevention ste are included in the Facility's PSM Plan, which is kept on-site as a separate document. Required elements include: 



Employee Participation; 

Process Safety Information; 

Process Hazard Analysis;

Operating Procedures;

Training;

Contractors; 

Pre-startup Review; 

Mechanical Integrity; 

Hot Work Permits;

Management of Change; 

Incident Investigation; and 

Compliance Audits.



FIVE-YEAR ACCIDENT HISTORY


The Midmar West Plant is a new RMP regulated facility and as such has had no accidental releases of flammable materials regulated under the RMP program that resulted in deaths, injuries, or significant property damage on-site, or off-site deaths, injuries, evacuations, sheltering in place, property damage or any environmental impact.


